<div style="text-align: right;"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+32</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div></div>
<br />
I decided to make an art page because why not?
<p>Most of the art here is probably going to be screenshots / clips from an SCP Animation <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I'm working on</span> that I need to get back to work on at some point. I also work on two SCP games so I may post some art from that if I can.</p>
<p>Most of the SCP art I have from before I started that animation are really old and look like shit so I will probably just shove that all in a collapsible as a &quot;see how far I've come&quot; kind of thing.</p>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc0"><span>SCP Pipedream</span></h3>
<p>This is the animation I mentioned earlier. I haven't been keeping track but if I had to guess, I'd say I put 50 to 150 hours into it. I think I started this in early 2018 or late 2017, but I only worked on it on-off for awhile before completely abandoning the project for a few months because I got distracted with other projects. I am hoping to finish up some stuff and get back to work on this so I can finish it and get it out the door.</p>
<p>The basic synopsis of the animation is &quot;Security guard goes on a drug trip&quot;. The entertainment is more from the trippy visuals of the animation rather than a story, but I do want to have a story in the background for you to pick up on. Before you ask, no I have never done drugs, other than coffee.</p>
<p>FYI I am making the animation in ToonBoom, with backgrounds made in Gimp.</p>
<p>Also, I am working on this project by myself, but I want to look into finding voice actors at some point down the line.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Security&nbsp;Guard&nbsp;Person</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This is (as of now) the very first frame of the animation.</p>
The security guard is heavily inspired by the security from containment breach. I would say the background, specifically the texturing, was inspired by how Lord Bung does his backgrounds.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/AIHK2Ux.png" alt="AIHK2Ux.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-086</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>SCP-086 is in the back there along with some miscellaneous shapes and illusions. This is the planned background for a scene near the end of the animation. (I added a border so it meshed better against the white background.)</p>
<div style="border: 1px solid #000;"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/MfbvAKl.png" alt="MfbvAKl.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-2146</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">This was in that confinement music special so I thought I would try and make it a trend to have in animations for SCP. Gotta include that 2146 reference.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/s2gqMIr.png" alt="s2gqMIr.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-312</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">Lucky you! You get to see some actual <em>animation!</em> It a bit low res because I cropped it from a larger scene but this is SCP-312 floating around in space. I think one of the frames may have also gotten removed when I converted it to a gif. It looks slightly choppier than in ToonBoom.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/94m3OOJ.gif" alt="94m3OOJ.gif" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-Not-A-Real-SCP</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This isn't an SCP on the site. It doesn't have a number. It is an SCP that appears during the first few scenes of the animation. This was a concept art for it, not actually from the animation, which is why it looks a bit pixely.</p>
You could probably guess where the name &quot;Pipe Dream&quot; comes from at this point.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/gP3d8c1.png" alt="gP3d8c1.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Animation&nbsp;Frame</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">This is a frame from around the middle of the animation. Go ahead and theorize about what is going on here.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/vNuKNDg.png" alt="vNuKNDg.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Another&nbsp;Animation&nbsp;Frame</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">This is another animation frame from one of the trippier parts of the animation. The background is taken from the Mandelbrot set but I need to get higher quality images for that at some point.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/A1ftkAP.png" alt="A1ftkAP.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc1"><span>SCP Games</span></h3>
<p>I work in the concept art department for SCP Ascension but I don't have anything of my own to show here. All of that is under lock and chain.</p>
<p>I also work on a game called SCP Foundation Command which is pretty early in development. I do graphics for it but most of what I've done so far is concept / placeholder since we are still very early.</p>
<p>The game is similar to Prison Architect except you build an SCP site facility instead of a prison, so of course there has to be D-Class. Here is a mock-up for a D-Class design.</p>
<p>The plan is to have a wide variety of body and face types so most of them won't have an ugly ass chin.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">D-Class</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/C39wlrs.png" alt="C39wlrs.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc2"><span>Other SCP stuff</span></h3>
<p>Here is an abandoned animation project called &quot;Project Shotgun&quot;. It was going to take place in the Bellerverse but I realized my plans were way too ambitious and unachievable so I abandoned it and reworked a lot of my ideas into Pipe Dream.</p>
<p>There is nothing but a green screen for the second half of the video because I exported the video wrong.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2RgR8R0awFQ&amp;t=1s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2RgR8R0awFQ&amp;t=1s</a></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Old&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;art</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/0GzhTHl.png" alt="0GzhTHl.png" class="image" /><br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/EjfTFAS.png" alt="EjfTFAS.png" class="image" /><br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/MrYHNcF.png" alt="MrYHNcF.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<h3 id="toc3"><span>Misc.</span></h3>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Jeffeffe</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This isn't an SCP related thing but I am really proud of it and it looks like it could be an SCP so I'm including it on my page.</p>
Also I named it Jeffeffe because I think it's funny.<br />
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/bKCrNgD.png" alt="bKCrNgD.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>

